## Description
The **Advanced Script **operator allows to insert, through the configuration settings, Java or RhinoScript code to transform input data.

## **Input**
**Input**

**Data type**

**Description**

**in0**

String

The input node on which to apply the Java or RhinoScript code specified in the configuration settings.

**inâ€¦**

String

N-th input node on which to apply the Java or RhinoScript code specified in the configuration settings.

## **Output**
**Output**

**Data type**

**Description**

**&lt;&gt;Record**

String

The transformed value obtained by applying the specified Java or RhinoScript code.

**&lt;&gt;out1**

String

N-th output, containing the transformed value obtained by applying the specified Java or RhinoScript code.

## **Settings**
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Inputs **section, click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) to add an input node to the list.

- In the **Outputs **section, click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) to add an output field to the list.

- In the **Script **section:

From the **Language **drop-down menu, select the language to use:

**Javascript**

- **Java**

> Tip

Java is usually preferred.

- If you selected "Java", specify the name of the Java class to use in the **Class **text field that appears next to the drop-down menu.

- In the **Value **text area, enter the code snippet that you want to apply to the input data.

> Note

For example, the following Java code parses input data, verifying whether they are within a specific interval, and then returns the corresponding element in a lookup table.

**Example: Java code**

`import it.ebilling.esource.core.CatalogOptions; import it.ebilling.esource.core.ICatalog;
import it.ebilling.esource.core.ICatalogResource;
import it.ebilling.esource.pipeline.mangler.hiter.HNodeImpl; import it.ebilling.esource.pipeline.mangler.hiter.functors. JavaHelper;
import java.util.ArrayList; import java.util.HashMap; import java.util.List; import java.util.Map;
import it.ebilling.esource.core.logging.LogFactory;
/**
*
*
*/
public class FunctoreCodeFascia extends JavaHelper {
private ICatalog dictionary; List&lt;Map&lt;String, String&gt;&gt; results
@Override
public void execute() {
//if (root.getChildren().get("in0") == null || root. getChildren().get("in0").get(0) == null ||
//root.getChildren().get("in1") == null || root.getChildren(). get("in1").get(0) == null ||
//root.getChildren().get("in2") == null || root.getChildren(). get("in2").get(0) == null) {
//return;
//}
/* read input */
// area geo
String in0 = root.getChildren().get("in0").get(0).getValue();
// flagfolder
String in1 = root.getChildren().get("in1").get(0).getValue();
// numero pagine
String in2 = root.getChildren().get("in2").get(0).getValue(); int numeroFogli = Integer.parseInt(in2);
String out1 = "";
HNodeImpl&lt;String&gt; outRoot = new HNodeImpl&lt;String&gt;(); result.add(outRoot);
HNodeImpl&lt;String&gt; record = new HNodeImpl&lt;String&gt;(); outRoot.addChild("Record", record);
if ((in0 == null || in0.equals("")) || (in1 == null || in1. equals(""))
|| (in2 == null || in2.equals(""))) { return;
}
try {
if (dictionary == null) {
Map&lt;String, String&gt; opts = new HashMap&lt;String, String&gt;(); opts.put(CatalogOptions.USE_LITERAL_WHITESPACE, "true"); dictionary = getExecutionContext().getConfiguration()
.getResourceById("PESO_TARIFFA")
.getAdapter(ICatalogResource.class).open(opts);
// carico tutti i dati del catalogo results = dictionary.getAll();
}
// per ogni risultato verifico se il cap cade in un certo intervallo
// capMin/capMax
// se si, restituisco il campo AREA_GEO, altrimenti restituisco -1
HNodeImpl&lt;String&gt; node1 = new HNodeImpl&lt;String&gt;(); for (Map&lt;String, String&gt; entry : results) {
String vettore = entry.get("VETTORE"); String areaGeo = entry.get("AREA_GEO"); String flagFolder = entry.get("FLAGFOLDER");
String lowerFogli = entry.get("LOWER_FOGLI"); String upperFogli = entry.get("UPPER_FOGLI"); String codeFascia = entry.get("CODE_FASCIA");
int lowerFogliInt = Integer.parseInt(lowerFogli); int upperFogliInt = Integer.parseInt(upperFogli);
if (vettore.equals("1") &amp;&amp; in0.equals(areaGeo)
&amp;&amp; in1.equals(flagFolder)
&amp;&amp; (numeroFogli &gt;= lowerFogliInt &amp;&amp; numeroFogli &lt;= upperFogliInt)) {
node1.setValue(codeFascia); record.addChild("@out1", node1); return;
}
}
node1.setValue("-1"); record.addChild("@out1", node1);
} catch (Exception ex) { LogFactory.getLog(FuntoreAreaGeografica.class).error( "During execution", ex);
}
}
}`
- Click **Apply **to confirm.
